  "commentary": "With SPX spot at 6593 sitting just below the massive +5811.5M gamma wall at 6600, dealers are positioned to sell any rally attempt into that level, creating strong resistance. The PIN regime confirms dealers are long gamma and will provide stabilizing flows - selling the 6600-6610 zone and buying any dip toward the 6500 negative gamma wall at -4463.8M. The recent GEX surge (197% in 1-min) suggests heavy options flow is reinforcing these levels, making 6500-6600 the key range with diminished volatility expected within this corridor.\n\nBottom line: expect the market to get pinned between 6500-6600 with muted moves.",
